		<td><b>Re: Space Race</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Famicom multitap is astoundingly simple:<br />Simply connect an ordinary controller to D1 instead of D0.<br /><br />NES multitap isn't too hard if you can build all-new hardware and don't require being able to plug in existing controllers. <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Four_Score#Building_new_hardware_from_scratch" class="postlink">(nesdevwiki)</a><br /><br />It's still not that hard if you <em>do</em> want to use existing controllers, but it requires an actual schematic (as well as donor sockets).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


